Desmodium dichotomum

    Authority
      Family
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 13690

   Notes
   DESCRIPTION: Herbaceous with branched angular stems which are
   moderately to densely pubescent with long tapering hairs. Leaves
   trifoliolate, leaflets ovate to elliptical, terminal leaflet 1.8ˆ8 cm
   long and 2ˆ6 cm wide, lateral leaflets 1.2ˆ7 cm long and 1.0ˆ4.8 cm
   wide. Flowers pink or blue and small. USE: Potential annual ley legume
   or forage crop. Extremely palatable and selectively grazed. GROWING
   PERIOD: Annual or perennial. COMMON NAMES: Desmodium. FURTHER INF:
   Found in Cameroon, Chad, Ethiopia, Sudan, Uganda, China ˆ Yunnan,
   India., Myanmar, Indonesia ˆ Celebes and Java. Found in dry tropical
   and subtropical environments. Dry matter yields in southern Queensland
   have ranged from 2ˆ6 t/ha/year.

   Sources
   Tropical forages 2005

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
